He was a hero.

13:47.094 --> 13:50.063
Very impressive.

13:50.097 --> 13:52.565
Well, hi, Mom.

13:52.599 --> 13:54.968
Oh, that reminds me.
It's time for cocktails.

13:55.002 --> 13:56.836
See you in a few.

13:56.870 --> 13:58.638
It's only 1:00.

13:58.671 --> 14:00.740
That's not true
about Sean's ancestors.

14:00.773 --> 14:02.475
I know.
They're from Canada.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.344
Robert Smalls was a guy
we learned about last year

14:04.377 --> 14:06.679
during Black History Month.
Why did you lie?

14:06.713 --> 14:09.349
I don't know. I was kind of
tired of listening to

14:09.382 --> 14:13.086
a white guy talk about
his slave-owning relatives.

14:13.120 --> 14:16.523
Okay, well, unfortunately,

14:16.556 --> 14:19.092
we have to stay here
a little longer than I thought.

14:19.126 --> 14:21.828
Why is your grandma
from England?

14:21.861 --> 14:23.563
Will you give us
a second, Jacob?

14:23.596 --> 14:26.099
[ Fred barks ]

14:26.133 --> 14:28.101
[ Sighs ]

14:28.135 --> 14:29.903
Everything okay?
No.

14:29.937 --> 14:32.339
Daniela and Sofia ran away.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.942
They're mad at Ava.
It's something to do with Teo,

14:34.975 --> 14:36.709
but the reception kept
cutting out.

14:36.743 --> 14:39.746
-Where are they?
-The bus station in Savannah.

14:41.481 --> 14:43.283
They want to come
live with us.
[ Fred barks ]

14:43.316 --> 14:44.784
Holy shit.
I know.

14:44.817 --> 14:46.619
I told them to wait there,
so we need to go.

14:46.653 --> 14:48.788
-Did you get the money?
-Not yet.

14:48.821 --> 14:50.123
-Why?
-It's tricky.

14:50.157 --> 14:51.758
You said she would just
give it to you.

14:51.791 --> 14:54.027
She will, but I can't look like
I just came for the money.

14:54.061 --> 14:55.528
I have to find
the right time to ask.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.564
Now is a good time.
I have to go to the girls.

14:57.597 --> 15:02.569
I know. Okay, you go. I'll stay
with Jacob and get the money.

15:02.602 --> 15:04.271
Look --

15:04.304 --> 15:06.139
I'll get it by the end
of the night,

15:06.173 --> 15:08.141
and then we're home free.

15:08.175 --> 15:12.445
**

15:16.516 --> 15:17.717
[ Mutters ]

15:17.750 --> 15:19.419
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

15:19.452 --> 15:21.821
[ Laughs ]

15:21.854 --> 15:23.923
Mm. It's your girlfriend.

15:23.957 --> 15:25.993
[ Vibrating continues ]
She's not my girlfriend.

15:26.026 --> 15:28.761
Her name is Letty.
[ Chuckles ]

15:28.795 --> 15:31.431
Stop defending her.

15:31.464 --> 15:34.734
You better be standing outside
with a trunk full of cash.

15:34.767 --> 15:37.570
Can you see what I'm wearing?
No.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.273
A seafoam green
bridesmaid's dress.

15:40.307 --> 15:42.842
Remember that bachelorette
video in the Sprinter?

15:42.875 --> 15:46.113
My sister Mary Ann is getting
married to some fucknugget

15:46.146 --> 15:47.614
from New Jersey.

15:47.647 --> 15:49.616
-Wedding is tonight.
-That's nice.

15:49.649 --> 15:51.451
No, not nice.

15:51.484 --> 15:53.620
Did you ever see
a 62-year-old Bridezilla?

15:53.653 --> 15:55.022
It's a shit show.

15:55.055 --> 15:57.457
Where is my money?
That's why I'm calling.

15:57.490 --> 16:00.427
We got most of it, but I can't
bring you the whole amount

16:00.460 --> 16:01.928
until tomorrow.

16:01.961 --> 16:05.298
[ Sound machine plays
"wrong" tune ]

16:05.332 --> 16:07.834
[ Object thuds ]
[ Laughs ]

16:07.867 --> 16:10.537
Will you take 450?
I can get that to you now.

16:10.570 --> 16:12.772
This is not
the William Morris Agency.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.341
You don't get 10%.

16:14.374 --> 16:15.808
Please, just one more day.

16:15.842 --> 16:19.112
I swear, I'll have it
to you by tomorrow.

16:19.146 --> 16:21.681
Aren't you at the wedding
tonight, anyway?

16:23.683 --> 16:25.818
Tomorrow by 5:00,
and don't think I don't know

16:25.852 --> 16:27.987
exactly where you are.

16:28.021 --> 16:30.890
**

16:30.923 --> 16:35.862
Okay, yeah. Thanks.
Have fun at the wedding.

16:39.366 --> 16:41.334
Why can't it be our wedding?

16:41.368 --> 16:43.836
Why can't -- What?

16:43.870 --> 16:46.506
Why not us get married?

16:46.539 --> 16:49.042
Yeah, I know what this is.

16:49.076 --> 16:51.078
[ Glass thuds ]
This is that thing you do

16:51.111 --> 16:54.481
where you lead me down a path,
and I believe you,

16:54.514 --> 16:57.750
and then you smack me down
with peals of laughter.

16:57.784 --> 17:00.720
Obviously, we're not getting
fucking married.

17:00.753 --> 17:02.655
Oh, so romantic.

17:02.689 --> 17:05.358
I propose.

17:05.392 --> 17:10.063
And you doubt my intentions
with foul language.

17:11.398 --> 17:15.335
Why do you have tuxedos
for kids just lying around?

17:15.368 --> 17:18.538
Well, when you have as many
black-tie affairs as we do,

17:18.571 --> 17:20.407
you need backups.

17:20.440 --> 17:22.041
I Googled your ancestors.

17:22.075 --> 17:25.011
I found out your great-great
grandfather owned 600 slaves

17:25.044 --> 17:27.380
and died of something
called syphilis.

17:27.414 --> 17:30.883
Well, those were
different times.

17:30.917 --> 17:33.086
You look very handsome
in that tux.

17:33.120 --> 17:34.654
Thanks.

17:37.290 --> 17:39.226
Hmm.

17:39.259 --> 17:40.793
What?

17:43.763 --> 17:46.699
You're really up shit's creek.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.202
That money isn't for Jacob.

17:49.236 --> 17:53.273
It is, in a way.

17:53.306 --> 17:56.576
If I don't get it,
I'll never see him again.

17:56.609 --> 17:58.145
I'll be in prison.

17:58.178 --> 18:00.480
Well... [ Scoffs ]
That doesn't make much sense.

18:00.513 --> 18:04.551
Yeah, look, you don't
want me to explain it.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.953
So if you get the money,
what then?

18:06.986 --> 18:09.722
Off to the next scam?
No.

18:09.756 --> 18:11.958
We have a house.

18:11.991 --> 18:14.427
Jacob starts school next week.

18:14.461 --> 18:16.496
Javier has a job.

18:16.529 --> 18:18.298
He's a cook.

18:19.666 --> 18:21.801
And what are you going to do?

18:21.834 --> 18:24.437
Be Jacob's mom.

18:25.838 --> 18:29.142
Letty, look at me.

18:29.176 --> 18:31.278
Do you remember
how good I was?

18:31.311 --> 18:34.647
Alice Lewis. One of the great
uncredited jewel thieves

18:34.681 --> 18:36.283
in American history,
and in the '70s,

18:36.316 --> 18:38.518
I had a pretty good run
in Europe, to boot,

18:38.551 --> 18:40.920
but it wasn't all talent.

18:40.953 --> 18:44.291
I was young
and I needed that high.

18:44.324 --> 18:46.593
And it let me get away with
things I could never

18:46.626 --> 18:50.963
get away with now -- things
you're getting away with.

18:50.997 --> 18:54.201
Eventually,
I had to switch it up.

18:55.735 --> 18:59.872
So I'm just wondering...

18:59.906 --> 19:03.710
what is your game plan?

19:03.743 --> 19:06.713
To have my own family.

19:06.746 --> 19:09.416
To raise Jacob
into a good person.

19:11.083 --> 19:14.187
Why are you making me work
so hard for this?

19:14.221 --> 19:18.491
Because working is how
normal people make money.

19:21.027 --> 19:23.230
[ Object clatters ]

19:31.738 --> 19:36.343
[ Touchscreens clicking ]

19:40.680 --> 19:42.081
Hi.

19:42.114 --> 19:44.351
Oh, my...

19:44.384 --> 19:49.522
**

19:49.556 --> 19:51.391
My God, it's been so weird
not seeing you.

19:51.424 --> 19:53.393
I know. It's been weird
for me, too.

19:53.426 --> 19:54.861
We missed you.

19:54.894 --> 19:57.230
And I'm sure your mom
misses you right now.

19:57.264 --> 19:59.432
-No, she doesn't.
-She's probably scared to death.

19:59.466 --> 20:01.000
No, she's not.

20:01.033 --> 20:03.202
She hasn't noticed we're gone.
She hasn't even called us.

20:03.236 --> 20:06.205
[ Inhales deeply ]
Let's go.

20:06.239 --> 20:09.742
Don't make us go back.
He can't make us go back.

20:09.776 --> 20:11.778
No one can make us
do anything.

20:11.811 --> 20:15.548
This is America.

20:15.582 --> 20:17.717
Okay.

20:17.750 --> 20:20.219
Let's get some food.

20:22.422 --> 20:23.756
You don't get it.

20:23.790 --> 20:25.258
That Teo guy literally moved in.

20:25.292 --> 20:26.393
To our house.

20:26.426 --> 20:28.528
Your mother must've
wanted him to move in.

20:28.561 --> 20:32.632
Obviously. He clings to her
like a leech and she loves it.

20:32.665 --> 20:34.301
Doesn't sound like your mom.

20:34.334 --> 20:37.604
That's what we're trying to
tell you. She's not herself.

20:37.637 --> 20:39.272
And she can't even see it.

20:39.306 --> 20:41.040
Sometimes it's hard to
see yourself.

20:41.073 --> 20:44.076
But she can't even see
how gross he is.

20:44.110 --> 20:45.445
He thinks he's our dad.

20:45.478 --> 20:48.080
The guy showed up, like,
10 days ago,

20:48.114 --> 20:50.249
and now he's our dad
and lives in our house.

20:50.283 --> 20:51.651
Have you talked to your mom
about this?

20:51.684 --> 20:53.886
We can't even make eye contact
with her without him

20:53.920 --> 20:55.422
staring back at us.

20:55.455 --> 20:57.223
**

20:57.256 --> 20:59.592
Does it seem like Teo's
doing drugs?

21:02.261 --> 21:04.597
I mean, if you told me he was
a major druggie,

21:04.631 --> 21:06.799
I would be like, "Okay."

21:06.833 --> 21:09.101
Is he?

21:09.135 --> 21:11.438
Maybe that explains
the WiFi thing.

21:11.471 --> 21:12.939
What WiFi thing?

21:12.972 --> 21:16.275
He changed the password
to the WiFi in our house

21:16.309 --> 21:19.178
and then wouldn't give it
to us for, like, three hours.

21:19.211 --> 21:21.681
**

21:21.714 --> 21:24.551
Thank you.
Thank you.

21:26.486 --> 21:29.322
Okay.

21:29.356 --> 21:31.624
I still
have to call your mom.

21:31.658 --> 21:32.825
No!

21:32.859 --> 21:35.328
This will all be okay.
I promise.

21:38.164 --> 21:41.167
-Sofia, I need your phone.
-Why?

21:42.168 --> 21:44.537
She won't pick up
if it's him.

21:45.805 --> 21:46.973
Sure.

21:47.006 --> 21:49.075
Thank you.

21:50.677 --> 21:53.179
Sofi Tukker: * I think that
I'll keep loving you *

21:53.212 --> 21:55.348
* Way past 65
Where's the bar?

21:55.382 --> 21:57.717
Is drinking and driving
a good idea?

21:57.750 --> 22:00.219
If by driving, you mean
trying to fuck your husband.

22:00.252 --> 22:03.656
* You are my best friend and
we've got some shit to shoot *
Champagne?

22:03.690 --> 22:06.325
Ooh, thank you.
