22:06.359 --> 22:08.661
* That's the way it goes

22:08.695 --> 22:11.297
* It's just us two,
it's déjà vu *

22:11.330 --> 22:13.132
* It's what we know

22:13.165 --> 22:16.135
* That's the way we like it

22:16.168 --> 22:18.170
* Don't complicate

22:18.204 --> 22:21.374
* No need to fight it,
just invite it *

22:21.408 --> 22:23.242
* Yeah

22:23.275 --> 22:26.012
* I think that
I'll keep loving you *

22:26.045 --> 22:28.014
* Way past 65

22:28.047 --> 22:33.185
* We made a language for us two
we don't need to describe *

22:33.219 --> 22:37.824
* Every time you call on me,
I drop what I do *

22:37.857 --> 22:42.762
* You are my best friend and
we've got some shit to shoot *

22:42.795 --> 22:51.704
**

22:54.240 --> 22:57.710
[ Voice echoing ] Do you wanna
see what this is worth?

22:57.744 --> 23:01.748
[ Gasps, voice echoing ]
Total steal.
Right?

23:01.781 --> 23:03.850
That's worth at least 100 grand.

23:03.883 --> 23:10.122
**

23:10.156 --> 23:12.725
Vodka martini,
bruised with a twist.

23:12.759 --> 23:14.561
Man: Yes, ma'am.

23:14.594 --> 23:20.433
[ Indistinct conversations ]
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

23:23.102 --> 23:25.404
I told you, I'll have
the cash tomorrow.

23:25.438 --> 23:27.306
It's me -- Christian.

23:27.339 --> 23:30.076
It's me -- Christian.
Hi, Lefty.

23:31.243 --> 23:32.579
Are you okay?

23:32.612 --> 23:33.780
Guess what?

23:33.813 --> 23:35.314
I got married.

23:35.347 --> 23:37.884
No, you didn't.
You're drunk.

23:37.917 --> 23:40.052
You're at Lashever's
sister's wedding.

23:40.086 --> 23:42.889
I know, but we got married
on the way.

23:42.922 --> 23:44.957
You can... [ Laughs ]

23:44.991 --> 23:46.726
You can congratulate
us tomorrow

23:46.759 --> 23:50.229
when you bring me
my money by 5.
[ Laughing ]

23:50.262 --> 23:54.333
Or...or no more
Mrs. Nice Guy.

23:54.366 --> 23:56.302
[ Laughing ]

23:56.335 --> 23:57.970
[ Cellphone thuds ]

23:59.806 --> 24:02.141
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:02.174 --> 24:05.011
Can I actually get
another one? For a friend.

24:05.044 --> 24:06.746
Man: No problem.

24:06.779 --> 24:09.949
**

24:09.982 --> 24:13.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:15.321 --> 24:16.489
Oh, come on!
Oh!

24:16.523 --> 24:19.592
No, no, no...
[ Laughter ]

24:19.626 --> 24:21.027
Mm.

24:23.796 --> 24:26.332
Don't waste your time.

24:26.365 --> 24:30.136
He's obviously sleeping
with that girl.

24:30.169 --> 24:31.971
Miss Savannah Sperm Bank?

24:32.004 --> 24:33.540
Sweetheart...

24:33.573 --> 24:35.875
You don't think I already
barked up that twat?

24:35.908 --> 24:39.178
I need real intent
to penetrate.

24:39.211 --> 24:41.814
Fine. But if I can prove
she's sleeping with him,

24:41.848 --> 24:43.315
then I don't have to.

24:43.349 --> 24:47.687
However you get the job done,
but she beats him at tennis.

24:50.189 --> 24:52.358
You're off your game, babe.

24:52.391 --> 24:54.994
Having a kid'll do that.

24:55.027 --> 24:59.599
**

25:04.036 --> 25:06.873
* The sun went down,
but we stayed up *

25:06.906 --> 25:09.408
* We could never get enough
[ Chattering, laughter ]

25:09.441 --> 25:10.910
And stiff as a board.

25:10.943 --> 25:13.713
[ Laughs ] Never that,
never that.
[ Giggles ]

25:13.746 --> 25:15.481
Oh, Letty, come on over.

25:15.514 --> 25:20.052
Everyone, this is my...
Oh, no blood relation.

25:20.086 --> 25:21.588
Hey, hands off, bitch.

25:21.621 --> 25:24.657
R.J.'s mine.

25:24.691 --> 25:26.926
[ Laughs ]

25:26.959 --> 25:30.029
Me, but on "Southern Charm."

25:30.062 --> 25:31.230
[ Laughter ]

25:31.263 --> 25:33.065
So you're an actress?

25:33.099 --> 25:35.267
Mm? No.

25:35.301 --> 25:37.336
It's a reality show.

25:37.369 --> 25:39.906
Oh, so you're on
a reality show.

25:39.939 --> 25:42.408
No.

25:42.441 --> 25:46.078
R.J. and my granddaddy were
best friends growing up.

25:46.112 --> 25:48.514
And ever since
my granddaddy died,

25:48.547 --> 25:50.783
R.J. has been nothing
but good to me.

25:50.817 --> 25:52.418
Mm, mm, mm.
Mm.

25:52.451 --> 25:55.421
I love him more than,
like, anyone in the world.

25:55.454 --> 25:57.423
Oh.
[ Giggles ]

25:57.456 --> 25:59.091
Maybe they should
auction you off.

25:59.125 --> 26:01.060
Not a chance.

26:01.093 --> 26:02.962
He's priceless.

26:02.995 --> 26:04.797
[ Both laugh ]

26:04.831 --> 26:07.634
Is there any way you could
get me another champagne?

26:08.601 --> 26:10.703
Sure.
Thank you.

26:10.737 --> 26:13.072
[ Both giggle ]

26:13.105 --> 26:15.207
Isn't she a doll?

26:15.241 --> 26:17.644
You're a doll.
[ Giggles ]

26:21.648 --> 26:23.249
[ Door opens ]

26:23.282 --> 26:25.451
Let's go.
In the car now.

26:25.484 --> 26:28.788
-Oh, my God. Chill out.
-Now.

26:28.821 --> 26:30.589
Hi, Dad.

26:41.167 --> 26:42.969
Ava.

26:46.172 --> 26:49.776
Well, goodbye forever,
I guess.

26:49.809 --> 26:51.310
Not forever.

26:51.343 --> 26:59.351
**

26:59.385 --> 27:01.688
[ Speaking Spanish ]

27:03.355 --> 27:09.561
**

27:22.174 --> 27:24.610
You moved into
my sister's house.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.578
You accused me
of killing Silk.

27:30.683 --> 27:32.719
Are you doing coke again?

27:34.053 --> 27:36.723
I've been clean 15 years.

27:38.590 --> 27:41.360
Why did you change the WiFi
password in Ava's house?

27:41.393 --> 27:43.696
Because,
speaking of cocaine,

27:43.730 --> 27:46.532
have you noticed those girls
on their phones?

27:46.565 --> 27:49.836
Social media addiction is
an actual chemical thing.

27:49.869 --> 27:51.603
[ Chuckles ]

27:53.405 --> 27:55.574
[ Speaking Spanish ]

28:40.386 --> 28:43.589
And I...I don't judge.

28:43.622 --> 28:47.426
I know your life has been...
complicated.

28:47.459 --> 28:51.197
But I'll take care of Ava
and the girls.

28:51.230 --> 28:53.766
You take care of Letty
and Jacob.

28:55.401 --> 28:57.203
How do you know his name?

28:57.236 --> 28:59.906
Ava told me.

29:01.808 --> 29:04.911
You're lucky to have a new
family of your own.

29:06.145 --> 29:08.280
Go be with them.

29:08.314 --> 29:10.249
Ava will always be
my family.

29:10.282 --> 29:11.918
Of course she will.

29:11.951 --> 29:15.587
But you need
to give her time.

29:15.621 --> 29:19.125
And you need to give me
a chance.

29:19.158 --> 29:20.993
Please stay away.

29:21.027 --> 29:25.297
You do understand
who you are, right?

29:25.331 --> 29:28.400
I do.

29:28.434 --> 29:29.969
I'm the person people hire

29:30.002 --> 29:32.805
to kill people
who have fucked with them.

29:32.839 --> 29:37.309
Or hurt someone in their
family that they love.

29:37.343 --> 29:39.812
I'm very good at it.

29:39.846 --> 29:43.382
And they never,
ever see me coming.

29:45.617 --> 29:47.854
You can go now.

29:50.289 --> 29:52.925
[ Groans ]

29:52.959 --> 29:56.528
**

30:00.199 --> 30:02.501
**

30:02.534 --> 30:07.273
Everybody, this handsome lad
is my grandson.

30:07.306 --> 30:09.976
Great-grandson.
Yes, quite so.

30:10.009 --> 30:13.179
Great-grandson.
Isn't he the sweetest fellow?

30:13.212 --> 30:15.948
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

30:15.982 --> 30:18.684
Shall we play
some make-believe?

30:20.152 --> 30:24.223
Actually, he's from Zimbabwe.

30:24.256 --> 30:27.326
My granddaughter adopted him
from one of those villages

30:27.359 --> 30:28.560
with all the flies.

30:28.594 --> 30:30.329
It's just like
Angelina Jolie.

30:30.362 --> 30:32.865
Woman: What's his name?

30:32.899 --> 30:34.867
Imamu.

30:34.901 --> 30:37.136
I love it.
What does it mean?

30:37.169 --> 30:40.006
Oh, oh, no, no, no.
He -- he just got here.

30:40.039 --> 30:42.208
He doesn't speak much
English yet.

30:42.241 --> 30:44.076
But he's going to learn,
isn't he?

30:44.110 --> 30:46.012
Of course he is.

30:46.045 --> 30:50.216
Well, I can't sit here
all night or Alice will kill me.

30:50.249 --> 30:51.817
No.
[ Chuckles ]

30:51.850 --> 30:53.886
Well... [ Kisses ]
Bye, R.J.

30:53.920 --> 30:56.088
Yeah.

30:56.122 --> 30:57.890
**

30:57.924 --> 30:59.425
[ Chimes ]

31:01.293 --> 31:03.362
Okay, be honest.

31:03.395 --> 31:04.830
About what?

31:04.863 --> 31:06.432
You and R.J.

31:06.465 --> 31:08.234
He's a real sweetheart.

31:08.267 --> 31:09.535
And rich.

31:09.568 --> 31:11.437
So rich.

31:11.470 --> 31:14.773
I mean, it's kind of obvious
what's going on between you two.

31:14.806 --> 31:17.009
Don't worry, I'll keep
your secret,

31:17.043 --> 31:20.712
but you might want to
tone it down a little.

31:20.746 --> 31:24.850
Between me and R.J.?
[ Laughs ]

31:24.883 --> 31:26.919
Who have you been
talkin' to?

31:26.953 --> 31:29.788
No one.
I've been sitting here.

31:29.821 --> 31:33.926
Honey, my family owns
half of South Carolina.

31:33.960 --> 31:36.595
I don't need some
old man's money.

31:36.628 --> 31:39.598
He's sweet, and we flirt,

31:39.631 --> 31:42.734
but it's the South, babe,
it's what we do.

31:42.768 --> 31:46.372
That can't be all you do.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.474
You're right.

31:48.507 --> 31:51.210
I also go to him for
financial advice.

31:51.243 --> 31:54.880
He's not my type.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.615
Mm.

31:56.648 --> 31:58.817
That's my type.

32:00.419 --> 32:02.854
Savannah: Mm.

32:05.491 --> 32:06.658
Hey.

32:06.692 --> 32:09.461
What happened?
Are the girls okay?

32:09.495 --> 32:11.830
We'll talk later.
Let's go.

32:11.863 --> 32:13.565
Did you get the money?

32:13.599 --> 32:15.301
No. Not yet.

32:15.334 --> 32:16.969
Almost.
Almost?

32:17.003 --> 32:19.771
So when Letty telephoned
from Africa, I said,

32:19.805 --> 32:22.674
"You have got to adopt
that little boy."

32:22.708 --> 32:24.643
Woman:
She saved that boy's life.

32:24.676 --> 32:26.979
Do you know what?
He saved us right back.

32:27.013 --> 32:28.247
Oh.

32:28.280 --> 32:30.449
I'm taking Jacob
out of here.
Great.

32:30.482 --> 32:33.919
Hey, Jacob. Let's go. I need to
talk to you for a moment.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.687
[ Whispers ]
You have one hour.

32:35.721 --> 32:39.825
The boyfriend. They're thinking
of changing his name to Jacob.

32:39.858 --> 32:41.960
But I like "Imamu."

32:41.994 --> 32:51.937
**

32:51.970 --> 32:57.843
**

32:57.876 --> 33:01.013
* Must let

33:01.047 --> 33:02.514
* Me

33:02.548 --> 33:04.216
* Help

33:04.250 --> 33:09.288
* You

33:09.321 --> 33:11.590
No more champagne.

33:12.591 --> 33:18.664
* You

33:19.831 --> 33:21.567
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversations ]

33:21.600 --> 33:24.370
[ No accent ] That necklace was
donated by Bitsy Caldwell.

33:24.403 --> 33:26.238
It was an heirloom.

33:26.272 --> 33:29.475
[ Scoffs ] Whatever.

33:29.508 --> 33:31.810
They'll blame it on
a cater waiter.
My purse? Are you accusing me?

33:31.843 --> 33:33.712
Man: Oh, absolutely,
and you know what...

33:33.745 --> 33:36.715
R.J. isn't cheating on you.

33:36.748 --> 33:38.350
Not with Savannah, anyway.

33:38.384 --> 33:39.718
I told you that.

33:39.751 --> 33:41.520
Jesus, Letty!

33:41.553 --> 33:43.889
I give you a simple
goddamn job to do.

33:43.922 --> 33:47.126
I did a better job.

33:49.261 --> 33:51.697
I don't need any jewelry.

33:54.433 --> 33:56.768
I need to get outta here.

33:56.802 --> 33:59.671
It's worth $100,000.
You can have it for $50,000.

33:59.705 --> 34:01.907
I'm not playing with you,
girl.

34:01.940 --> 34:06.212
You just don't get it, do you?
I am done with all this.

34:06.245 --> 34:08.714
This is my last job.

34:08.747 --> 34:11.550
No more acting,
no more lying.

34:11.583 --> 34:14.386
Just goddamn tired.

34:14.420 --> 34:17.022
I want my own life back.

34:17.055 --> 34:20.392
Just me, myself,
and a villa in Portofino.

34:20.426 --> 34:24.096
And you're just gonna leave R.J.
with only 20% of his money?

34:24.130 --> 34:25.864
He'll be fine.

34:25.897 --> 34:29.635
[ Scoffs ]
You're heartless.

34:29.668 --> 34:32.638
Everyone has a heart.

34:32.671 --> 34:35.274
But I know mine.

34:35.307 --> 34:38.076
It's just like yours.

34:39.278 --> 34:42.814
It's only so big.

34:42.848 --> 34:44.816
And it wears you out.

34:45.817 --> 34:48.920
It wears other people out.

34:48.954 --> 34:51.423
And there's not a shot
in hell

34:51.457 --> 34:55.927
Javier won't bounce
when you finally wear him out.

34:55.961 --> 34:58.330
I don't need a lecture.

34:58.364 --> 35:00.332
Well, then, get back to work.

35:10.442 --> 35:15.947
**

35:15.981 --> 35:22.087
**

35:22.120 --> 35:23.489
[ Grunts ]
Yes.

35:23.522 --> 35:24.856
Ah!

35:24.890 --> 35:28.860
You know, Jacob, that was
wrong of Alice to make up

35:28.894 --> 35:31.129
that story about you.
It's okay.

35:31.163 --> 35:33.599
I think she just wanted
those people to like her.

35:33.632 --> 35:35.667
And it's fun to pretend
to be someone else.

35:35.701 --> 35:40.138
Yeah, I know, but lying
just leads to more lies.

35:40.172 --> 35:42.941
You should always tell
the truth if you can.

35:42.974 --> 35:45.777
Everybody lies.

35:45.811 --> 35:47.646
Not everybody.

35:47.679 --> 35:49.181
You do.

35:50.816 --> 35:53.118
I, uh...

35:53.151 --> 35:55.487
sometimes, yeah.

35:55.521 --> 35:58.357
We all do sometimes.

35:58.390 --> 36:03.329
But once you start to lie,
believe me,

36:03.362 --> 36:05.497
it is very difficult to stop.

36:05.531 --> 36:09.801
But if you stop now, you can
have a life that is truthful,

36:09.835 --> 36:13.639
a life where you can be
proud of who you are,

36:13.672 --> 36:16.475
where you don't have to
pretend to be someone else.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.711
So now I can use my real name
when I start my new school.

36:19.745 --> 36:24.983
**

36:25.016 --> 36:27.185
Let's talk to your mom
about that, hmm?

36:32.391 --> 36:35.261
-...been what? Illegal.
-Absolutely.

36:35.294 --> 36:37.829
Letty.
Later, gentlemen.

36:37.863 --> 36:40.999
Let's go for a walk. I haven't
seen the rest of your property.

36:41.032 --> 36:43.435
Just us.

36:43.469 --> 36:46.004
I don't think Javier
would like that.

36:46.037 --> 36:49.040
I'm not married to Javier.

36:49.074 --> 36:54.112
But I'm married...
to Alice.

36:56.582 --> 36:59.017
I'm -- I'm sorry. I gotta go.
Hmm.

36:59.050 --> 37:03.188
Letty, I know what
you're trying to do.

37:03.221 --> 37:06.858
And I know Alice
put you up to it.

37:06.892 --> 37:11.797
She's been trying to leave me
since the day we got married.

37:11.830 --> 37:13.299
Oh, come on.

37:13.332 --> 37:15.267
That British accent?

37:15.301 --> 37:17.536
Then why are you with her?

37:17.569 --> 37:21.540
'Cause I love her
in spite of it all.

37:21.573 --> 37:24.743
Maybe I love her
because of it all.

37:24.776 --> 37:26.378
And it doesn't bother you

37:26.412 --> 37:28.246
that she's trying to take
all your money?

37:28.280 --> 37:30.649
I haven't held on to my money
all these years

37:30.682 --> 37:34.486
by being some
silver-spooned idiot.

37:34.520 --> 37:39.124
I've always had my pick of women
because, well, you know,

37:39.157 --> 37:41.560
money and good looks.

37:41.593 --> 37:43.228
[ Chuckles ]

37:43.261 --> 37:46.231
But there's nobody
like Alice.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.934
She's a blast.

37:48.967 --> 37:52.070
[ Laughter ]
She's the woman I want to
finish this life with.

37:52.103 --> 37:54.740
[ Indistinct conversation,
laughter ]

37:54.773 --> 37:59.110
And if you found someone that
feels the same way about you,

37:59.144 --> 38:01.713
don't you throw him away.

38:03.449 --> 38:07.152
Oh, what's wrong?

38:07.185 --> 38:11.690
Alice was paying me to get
the goods on you.

38:11.723 --> 38:14.292
It's money I need to get out
of some deep shit.

38:14.326 --> 38:15.794
How much?

38:15.827 --> 38:18.830
$50,000.

38:20.632 --> 38:22.701
Cash okay?

38:24.302 --> 38:26.204
Y-Yeah.

38:26.237 --> 38:28.206
All right. Come with me.

38:32.478 --> 38:36.682
[ Dog barking in distance ]

38:36.715 --> 38:39.485
That was fun.
[ Sighs ] Yeah.

38:39.518 --> 38:41.487
You're getting to be
a very good player.

38:41.520 --> 38:43.054
You're pretty good, too.

38:43.088 --> 38:45.891
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

38:50.095 --> 38:53.164
[ Gun cocks ]
Ow, ow.

38:53.198 --> 38:54.833
[ Speaks Spanish ]

39:00.739 --> 39:04.576
[ Whimpering ]

39:04.610 --> 39:08.414
[ Speaking Spanish ]

39:09.581 --> 39:12.083
[ Whimpering ]

39:15.286 --> 39:18.790
[ Heavy breathing ]

39:22.394 --> 39:23.762
[ Thud ]
[ Grunts ]

39:23.795 --> 39:26.031
[ Gunshot ]
[ Groans ]

39:26.064 --> 39:29.034
[ Gun cocks ]
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:29.067 --> 39:32.370
[ Seat belt whooshing,
clicking ]

39:39.945 --> 39:42.781
It's okay, it's okay. Jacob,
listen to me. It's okay.

39:42.814 --> 39:45.016
It's okay. You're okay now.

39:45.050 --> 39:46.618
Jacob, listen to me, that man,

39:46.652 --> 39:48.119
he was just trying
to steal our car.

39:48.153 --> 39:50.522
Did you shoot him?
Yes. Just a little. Yes.

39:50.556 --> 39:52.190
Look at me, Jacob. It's okay.

39:52.223 --> 39:54.560
I'm gonna call your mom
to come get you, okay?

39:54.593 --> 39:56.194
And we're gonna
call the police.

39:56.227 --> 39:59.030
It's okay. We'll sit
for a minute.

39:59.064 --> 40:01.066
Let's just sit for a minute.

40:01.099 --> 40:04.936
Sit here for a minute,
that's it. That's it, buddy.

40:04.970 --> 40:06.738
That's it.
It's okay. It's okay.

40:06.772 --> 40:11.610
It's all good. I know.

40:11.643 --> 40:13.178
I know.

40:17.516 --> 40:20.018
[ Car door opens ]

40:23.254 --> 40:25.156
[ Faint indistinct
conversation ]

40:25.190 --> 40:29.461
I gotta hand it to you,
you got me on this one.

40:29.495 --> 40:32.464
[ Door closes ]
Well, we're the same.

40:32.498 --> 40:33.999
Not completely.

40:34.032 --> 40:36.835
Right.
You're 40 years older.

40:36.868 --> 40:39.170
[ Vehicle departs ]

40:39.204 --> 40:42.574
You really were like
a mother to me.

40:42.608 --> 40:47.178
Oh, sweetheart,
let's be real.

40:47.212 --> 40:49.848
I recruited you into
going on crime sprees.

40:49.881 --> 40:51.850
It doesn't mean
I don't love you,

40:51.883 --> 40:54.720
but I was nothing
like a mother.

40:56.387 --> 41:00.025
I've never told you this story
because, frankly,

41:00.058 --> 41:02.193
it's one I'd rather forget.

41:02.227 --> 41:04.462
But it was 1968.

41:04.496 --> 41:06.798
I was living with this guy

41:06.832 --> 41:09.367
who may or may not be
your grandfather.

41:09.400 --> 41:10.636
[ Chuckles ]

41:10.669 --> 41:14.039
And I was 7 1/2 months
pregnant with your mother.

41:14.072 --> 41:16.341
But it didn't show much
and I hid it really well,

41:16.374 --> 41:18.944
so nobody knew.

41:18.977 --> 41:21.813
We were living in a van.
[ Laughs ]

41:21.847 --> 41:23.615
And we had run out of
party money,

41:23.649 --> 41:26.718
so we decided that we would
stick up a liquor store.

41:26.752 --> 41:29.955
But the owner didn't mess around
and he started shooting at us

41:29.988 --> 41:31.456
with a double-barreled
shotgun.

41:31.489 --> 41:34.325
He caught Andy in the thigh,
I trip over a curb --

41:34.359 --> 41:36.327
Andy's the guy who might be
your grandfather --

41:36.361 --> 41:40.799
and I went down hard, and it
put me right into labor.

41:40.832 --> 41:44.570
But when I had Estelle,
I...

41:44.603 --> 41:48.239
I didn't give a second thought
about giving her up.

41:48.273 --> 41:51.242
I knew I couldn't
raise her.

41:51.276 --> 41:53.979
Even though she would hate me,
and I knew she'd hate me

41:54.012 --> 41:56.882
the rest of my life --
and the rest of hers.

41:56.915 --> 42:00.986
I knew I couldn't give up
chasing that --

42:01.019 --> 42:03.755
that rush of adrenaline.

42:03.789 --> 42:06.024
I couldn't give up the fun.

42:06.057 --> 42:08.594
I couldn't give up myself.

42:08.627 --> 42:10.095
And neither can you.

42:10.128 --> 42:13.765
We chose this life.
Estelle didn't.

42:13.799 --> 42:15.601
And neither did Jacob.

42:15.634 --> 42:18.870
You can't drag him around
with you while you and Javier

42:18.904 --> 42:21.006
do whatever the hell it is
you guys are doing.

42:21.039 --> 42:23.008
-I don't wanna hear this.
-But you have to.

42:23.041 --> 42:25.010
[ Voice breaking ]
No, I love Jacob.

42:25.043 --> 42:27.112
He's the most important thing
in my life.

42:27.145 --> 42:28.947
Love isn't always enough.

42:28.980 --> 42:30.381
I'll tell you who ended up

42:30.415 --> 42:32.684
being a good mother --
your mother.

42:32.718 --> 42:35.587
Of all people.

42:35.621 --> 42:38.023
Jacob belongs with her.

42:38.056 --> 42:41.326
And I think you know it.

42:44.262 --> 42:47.298
Go to hell. You didn't even
try to be a good mother.

42:47.332 --> 42:48.967
At least
I still have a chance.

42:49.000 --> 42:51.269
There's more than one way
to be a good mother.

42:51.302 --> 42:54.873
And if you think for one minute
you are ever going to have

42:54.906 --> 42:58.376
the last word with me...

42:58.409 --> 43:00.812
think again.

43:00.846 --> 43:03.114
[ Exhales ]

43:05.083 --> 43:08.153
[ Footsteps retreating ]

43:10.989 --> 43:16.828
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

43:16.862 --> 43:19.197
Where are you guys?

43:20.498 --> 43:22.968
**

43:23.001 --> 43:25.003
[ Engine roars ]

43:25.036 --> 43:26.604
[ Tires squeal ]

43:28.707 --> 43:31.843
[ Tires screech ]
[ Gasps ]

43:31.877 --> 43:33.544
[ Car door closes ]

43:35.213 --> 43:39.584
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

43:39.617 --> 43:43.288
He saw me shoot that guy
who tried to steal our car.

43:44.890 --> 43:47.592
[ Crying ]
Okay.

43:47.625 --> 43:49.928
Okay, I got you.
You're all right.

43:49.961 --> 43:53.031
The police are on their way.

43:53.064 --> 43:54.866
Just take him
back to Alice's house.

43:54.900 --> 43:57.769
I'll come get you when I finish
here with the police.

43:57.803 --> 43:59.337
Okay.

44:06.745 --> 44:11.049
[ Water dripping ]

44:12.751 --> 44:14.652
[ Exhales ]

44:14.686 --> 44:17.288
[ Coughs ]

44:17.322 --> 44:21.727
[ Heavy breathing ]

44:21.760 --> 44:23.528
[ Groans ]

44:27.332 --> 44:30.501
[ Ziptie zips ]
[ Groaning ]

44:33.204 --> 44:36.441
[ Groaning continues ]

44:38.109 --> 44:39.811
[ Fabric rips ]

44:39.845 --> 44:43.381
[ Heavy breathing ]

44:46.117 --> 44:51.456
[ Muffled groaning ]

44:55.693 --> 44:58.296
[ Ziptie zips ]

45:01.132 --> 45:03.701
[ Speaking Spanish ]

45:10.942 --> 45:13.044
[ Heavy breathing ]

45:13.078 --> 45:20.151
**

45:27.458 --> 45:31.429
[ "This Beautiful Life"
by Colony House playing ]

45:31.462 --> 45:34.465
**

45:34.499 --> 45:40.071
* What in the world
are we doing here? *

45:41.239 --> 45:46.677
* What is the meaning
of it all? *

45:48.513 --> 45:51.482
* To fall in love,
to make a life *

45:51.516 --> 45:55.120
* That's calm and stable

45:55.153 --> 46:00.691
* Or just to find a place
where I belong? *

46:03.094 --> 46:06.832
* All that I know

46:06.865 --> 46:10.468
* All that I see

46:10.501 --> 46:13.972
[ Seatbelt clicks ]
-Where are we going?

46:14.005 --> 46:17.608
* Inside of me

46:17.642 --> 46:18.977
Nana's.

46:19.010 --> 46:21.746
* All that I've done

46:21.779 --> 46:25.250
We're taking you home.

46:25.283 --> 46:29.020
* There must be more to this

46:29.054 --> 46:30.956
* Wonderful

46:30.989 --> 46:33.024
* Terrible

46:33.058 --> 46:37.195
* Beautiful

46:37.228 --> 46:39.397
* Life

46:45.136 --> 46:55.113
**

46:55.146 --> 47:05.356
**

47:05.390 --> 47:14.332
**
